        "comment": {
            "name": "comment",
            "type": "com.atlassian.jira.issue.fields.CommentSystemField",
            "value": [
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/48687",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=adamlundrigan",
                        "name": "adamlundrigan",
                        "displayName": "Adam Lundrigan",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "It would appear that the fix for ZF-9289 ([this commit|http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/code\/diff.php?repname=Zend+Framework&path=%2Ftrunk%2Flibrary%2FZend%2FFilter%2FInput.php&]) is the source of this notice. \r\n\r\nI've also noticed that the format you use to define {{$validators}} is not one of the approved formats from the manual ([see here|http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/manual\/en\/zend.filter.input.html#zend.filter.input.declaring]); in your example the 'perms' key is an array but the first element is not the name of a validator class.\r\n\r\nAs 'perms' in your example doesn't represent a valid validator entry, it should be silently ignored as was the case pre-ZF-9289.  I suggest a fix like this, which short-circuits the code addition of ZF-9289 if $rule[$classkey] is undefined:\r\n{code}\r\nIndex: library\/Zend\/Filter\/Input.php\r\n===================================================================\r\n--- library\/Zend\/Filter\/Input.php       (revision 24503)\r\n+++ library\/Zend\/Filter\/Input.php       (working copy)\r\n@@ -851,11 +851,13 @@\r\n                     if (is_array($rule)) {\r\n                         $keys      = array_keys($rule);\r\n                         $classKey  = array_shift($keys);\r\n-                        $ruleClass = $rule[$classKey];\r\n-                        if ($ruleClass === 'NotEmpty') {\r\n-                            $foundNotEmptyValidator = true;\r\n-                            \/\/ field may not be empty, we are ready\r\n-                            break 1;\r\n+                        if ( isset($rule[classKey]) ) {\r\n+                            $ruleClass = $rule[$classKey];\r\n+                            if ($ruleClass === 'NotEmpty') {\r\n+                                $foundNotEmptyValidator = true;\r\n+                                \/\/ field may not be empty, we are ready\r\n+                                break 1;\r\n+                            }\r\n                         }\r\n                     }\r\n{code}\r\n",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=adamlundrigan",
                        "name": "adamlundrigan",
                        "displayName": "Adam Lundrigan",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2011-10-13T17:28:03.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2011-10-13T17:28:03.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/48688",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=idealarron",
                        "name": "idealarron",
                        "displayName": "Arron Woods",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "{quote}\r\nAs 'perms' in your example doesn't represent a valid validator entry, it should be silently ignored as was the case pre-ZF-9289. I suggest a fix like this, which short-circuits the code addition of ZF-9289 if $rule[$classkey] is undefined:\r\n{quote}\r\n\r\nAgreed, I checked the manual and it was definitely an incorrect definition for 'perms'. I've updated this in my app already.\r\n\r\nThe notice is thrown even if I define a validator for perms though, for example:\r\n\r\n{code:title=Broken}\r\n$validators = array(\r\n    'html' => array('NotEmpty', 'presence' => 'required'),\r\n    'perms' => array('Int', 'default' => array()),\r\n);\r\n{code}\r\n\r\nOnly if I set 'default' to a string\/null\/boolean does the notice disappear:\r\n\r\n\r\n{code:title=Working}\r\n$validators = array(\r\n    'html' => array('NotEmpty', 'presence' => 'required'),\r\n    'perms' => array('Int', 'default' => 'foo'),\r\n);\r\n{code}",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=idealarron",
                        "name": "idealarron",
                        "displayName": "Arron Woods",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2011-10-13T17:49:29.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2011-10-13T17:49:29.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/48693",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=adamlundrigan",
                        "name": "adamlundrigan",
                        "displayName": "Adam Lundrigan",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "That is due to fact that the code added in ZF-9289 (spec. Line 851) only operates when {{$rule}} (the value part of any key-value pair) is an array, but fails to check whether that array contains the requested key before trying to use it, so when passed an empty array it emits a notice.  The fix I suggested above should take care of that problem. ",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=adamlundrigan",
                        "name": "adamlundrigan",
                        "displayName": "Adam Lundrigan",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2011-10-14T14:29:45.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2011-10-14T14:29:45.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/48694",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=adamlundrigan",
                        "name": "adamlundrigan",
                        "displayName": "Adam Lundrigan",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Fixed in trunk r24504 r24506.\r\nMerged to release-1.11 in r24505 r24507.\r\n\r\nZF2 pull request: https:\/\/github.com\/zendframework\/zf2\/pull\/500",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=adamlundrigan",
                        "name": "adamlundrigan",
                        "displayName": "Adam Lundrigan",
                        "active": true
                    },
